<section>
    <h2>Description</h2>
    <p>The <code>&lt;sub&gt;</code> element specifies inline text which should be displayed as subscript for solely typographical reasons. Subscripts are typically rendered with a lowered baseline using smaller text. Common uses include chemical formulas, mathematical expressions (like variable subscripts), and footnote references.</p>
    <p>Use <code>&lt;sub&gt;</code> only for typographical conventions, not for purely presentational purposes. For styling purposes, use CSS (<code>vertical-align: sub</code>).</p>
  </section>

